  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***flashback*** is a [scene](./scene.md) set in the past, interrupting the present-time narrative to dramatize an earlier event. Unlike [backstory](./backstory.md) delivered through exposition or dialogue, a flashback shows the past in real time — the reader experiences it as a scene rather than being told about it.",
